dcterms:creator: K. Payette
A. Jakab
dcterms:description: The FeTA dataset consists of 80 subjects, among which are 40 reconstructed using MIALSRTK and 40 using Simple-IRTK. Expert annotators delineated seven tissue labels including external cerebrospinal fluid (eCSF), gray matter (GM), white matter (WM), ventricles, cerebellum, deep GM, and brainstem.
dcterms:title: FeTA dataset

dcterms:creator: K. Payette
dcterms:description: The Clinical 1.5T dataset (CHUV) contains 40 subjects reconstructed with MIALSRTK and manually annotated following the FeTA protocol. Data was retrospectively collected from acquisitions done between January 2013 to April 2021.
dcterms:title: Clinical 1.5T dataset (CHUV)

dcterms:description: The Clinical 0.55T dataset (KCL) includes 40 neurotypical cases acquired on a low-field scanner. Subjects were reconstructed using two novel methods, NeSVoR and SVRTK. There are no available manual segmentations for this dataset.
dcterms:title: Clinical 0.55T dataset (KCL)

dcterms:creator: K. Payette
dcterms:description: The MICCAI 2022 FETA challenge dataset is part of the multi-center fetal brain tissue annotation challenge, which includes data from various institutions and was used to evaluate segmentation methods.
dcterms:title: MICCAI 2022 FETA challenge dataset
